		<tr>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				Just play whatever Race you want to Roleplay the most.  If you like elves, play a high elf. If you like little bald chubby people, play a gnome.  If you want to be evil, or just like Drow elves, play a Dark Elf.  Or Erudite if you like variations on the human race.  It's all about Roleplaying, not about PowerPlaying.  Picking the race that has the most intelligence isn't going to make the game fun, it's going to make it a big powerleveling session.  Don't do that.  Anyways, at high levels, wearing alot of items to boost intelligence, you can have 200 which is the mana max.  And in that case, you'd have the same amount of mana as the erudite or gnome or whatever it may be.  Basically, you get what you put in out of the game.  Just have fun!		

